					&lt;/tbody&gt;
				&lt;/table&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Coming to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Portland, OR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					August 10-12, 2010&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Chicago, IL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					October 26-28, 2010&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Oil Analysis Blunders. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Don&amp;#39;t Let These Happen to You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;ul&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;
						A large steel mill wanted to make every machine ready for easy oil sampling. After installing more than 1,200 new oil sampling ports, it began getting strange data on oil analysis reports. After investigating, it found that each of the new sampling ports was installed in the wrong location.&lt;/li&gt;
					&lt;li&gt;
						A company that had been using oil analysis for several years wondered why it was never able to detect pending bearing failures. After a bearing failure shut down production for more than a day, it discovered that the oil analysis tests being conducted were not capable of detecting impending failure. Instead, the tests were designed to identify wrong or degraded lubricants only.&lt;/li&gt;
				&lt;/ul&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;The Experts Agree&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					Oil analysis offers far superior early warning signals than other maintenance tools - including vibration analysis. Learn how to get maximum benefits at this intensive three day course.&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;What You Get When You Attend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;384-Page Course Manual &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					You&amp;rsquo;ll receive a course manual (a $395 value) to use as your textbook during the course and then take home for future reference. With 259 charts, tables and worksheets and 540 illustrations and photos, you&amp;rsquo;ll consider it an indispensable on-the-job reference for years to come.&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Oil Sampling Frequency Generator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					Noria&amp;rsquo;s exclusive Oil Sample Frequency Generator is used in oil analysis programs around the world to determine optimum oil sampling frequencies.&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Machine Life Extension Table&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					During the training, you&amp;rsquo;ll learn how to achieve up to 10X machine life extension for gearboxes, bearings, diesel engines, turbo machinery, and hydraulic system components. You&amp;rsquo;ll use this reference table to help plan and manage your machine life extension efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Want Certification?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					Optional Level II MLA certification testing is offered the day following the training by the &lt;a href="http://emailactivity.ecn5.com/engines/linkfrom.aspx?b=265125&amp;amp;e=39918187&amp;amp;l=http://www.lubecouncil.org"&gt;International Council for Machinery Lubrication&lt;/a&gt;. If you meet the &lt;a href="http://emailactivity.ecn5.com/engines/linkfrom.aspx?b=265125&amp;amp;e=39918187&amp;amp;l=http://lubecouncil.org/mlaii/mla2require.asp"&gt;requirements&lt;/a&gt; for this certification, Level I certification may not be necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Oil Analysis Basics is coming to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Portland, OR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;August 10-12, 2010&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Chicago, IL&lt;br /&gt;
					October 26-28, 2010&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					See the &lt;a href="http://emailactivity.ecn5.com/engines/linkfrom.aspx?b=265125&amp;amp;e=39918187&amp;amp;l=http://www.noria.com/training/oa/outlines.asp"&gt;course outline&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="http://emailactivity.ecn5.com/engines/linkfrom.aspx?b=265125&amp;amp;e=39918187&amp;amp;l=http://www.noria.com/training/oa/oa2010.pdf"&gt;view the brochure&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;p&gt;
					&lt;strong&gt;Questions?&lt;/strong&gt;Call 800-597-5460 or email &lt;a href="mailto:registrations@noria.com"&gt;registrations@noria.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
