	2 &amp;ldquo;Machinery Surveillance Employing Sonic/Ultrasonic Sensors&amp;rdquo; by J. C. Robinson, J. B. Van Voorhis, K. R. Piety, and W. King, Reliability Week 1999.&lt;br /&gt;
	3 &amp;ldquo;Monitoring Lubrication Using a Multi-Frequency Sonic/Ultrasonic Sensor&amp;rdquo; by Ray Garvey, Computational Systems Inc.&lt;br /&gt;
	3 Three case studies from &amp;ldquo;Advanced Vibration and Autocorrelation Analysis for Improved Diagnostics&amp;rdquo;; James Robinson, Bob Cook, James Crow; Emerson Global Users Exchange, 2006&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/predictive_maintenance/~4/p4BRiNSYgc8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2010-04-13T11:49:04-05:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/23990/pdm-technologies-optimize-lube" />
